reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 24, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great Starter Router!
reviews.reviewText: The set up was very easy and straight forward and it worked with my existing modem which was a plus. The app made it very easy to change and configure the WIFI passwords and names. Not to mention that its CRAZY fast. For the price point this is a no brainer.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 10, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Setup was a breeze
reviews.reviewText: I was pretty skeptical about purchasing a router to install myself as I have had issues with self-installation in the past. NETGEAR has such an easy setup process with the Nighthawk app, I was done within 10 minutes. I also love the ability to log into the app and review internet speeds, devices connected, parental controls and even a guest wifi option! I am very pleased with this purchase.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 10, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Works great. Nice compromise.
reviews.reviewText: My NTGR R7000 finally stopped working after 9 years. Tested the RAX50 and RAX30 with my home equipment (laptop, tablets, phones, roku) that supports wifi AC and N. I don't have any equipment that supports AX. I found both work well, providing over 200Mbps on 5GHz band. Very good range in my 2K foot house. The RAX30, takes up less room on my desk so kept the RAX30. Bought NTGR b-grade for $109 which is good price. I'm happy with this purchase. Hope it lasts 5 years.

reviews.reviewText: Excellent WIFI RouterBy Roy Lambrecht12345Very simple to hookup and install! I couldnt believe the differnce in performance once installed! No more performance drops while watching TV! Streaming now is perfect! Thanks, NETGEAR!!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Had some difficulty getting it set up but since then it's worked great!
reviews.reviewText: This router had a really difficult time getting up and running but after an hour with a customer service agent, we were able to get it up and running. It hasn't caused me any trouble since then and I find very few spotty moments with my wifi (obviously there are other factors at play too).It's a good product if you can be patient enough to get it set up initially.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 30, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Do not buy this unless you intend to use and pay for the security app. There is no way to use it otherwise. I already have a security program I trust and had no need to pay for another, so I returned it.
